<p>As asked here <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7074/whats-the-difference-between-string-and-string">What&#39;s the difference between String and string?</a> you can use string and String in the code.</p>  <p>To have a common code style, we decided to use string when we create objects:</p>  <pre><code>string name="Elvis"; </code></pre>  <p>and String when we use a static method:</p>  <pre><code>String.Concat("Elvis", " lives"); </code></pre>  <p>I wanted to configure ReSharper in order to recognize this but I just find that I can configure it to use either the first or the second way:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/0wikh.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/0wikh.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>